  "issue_title": "[Bug] Mirror issue-discovery spam count ignores open issues older than lookback window",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nMirror issue discovery currently uses the same lookback-bounded `/issues` response for two separate responsibilities:\n\n1. Scoring recent solved/closed issues.\n2. Counting currently open issues for the open-issue spam multiplier.\n\nThose windows should be separate. The scoring window should remain lookback-bounded, but the open-issue spam count should represent the miner's current open issue load across mirror-enabled repos, regardless of issue age.\n\nToday `run_mirror_issue_discovery()` calls `client.get_miner_issues(..., since=lookback_date)` and derives `total_open_issues` from that same response. The mirror `/issues` endpoint filters `OPEN` issues by `created_at >= since`, so still-open issues created before `PR_LOOKBACK_DAYS` are omitted from `total_open_issues` and do not affect `calculate_open_issue_spam_multiplier()`.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Give a miner enough valid solved issues in a mirror-enabled repo to pass issue-discovery eligibility.\n2. Have the same miner keep more than the allowed open-issue threshold open in mirror-enabled repos, with those open issues created before the lookback window.\n3. Run mirror issue discovery.\n4. Observe that `evaluation.total_open_issues` excludes those older open issues and the open-issue spam multiplier does not trip.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nIssue scoring should use the lookback-bounded issue list.\n\nOpen-issue spam counting should use the miner's current open issue count across mirror-enabled repos, independent of the scoring lookback window.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nThe open-issue spam count is derived from the same lookback-bounded issue list used for scoring. Old still-open issues get a free pass because they are absent from the response used to populate `total_open_issues`.\n\nIn a local repro, six current open issues correctly zeroed the issue-discovery score when present in the response. When those same open issues were omitted by the lookback window, the miner received a non-zero issue-discovery score.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: N/A\n- Python version: N/A\n- Commit/Version: current `test` branch\n\n## Additional Context\n\nPR #796 called this out as an out-of-scope follow-up: mirror open-issue count for the spam multiplier is currently sourced from the lookback-bounded `/issues` response, so a miner with open issues older than 35 days gets a free pass.\n\nFix direction: keep issue scoring lookback-bounded, but source `total_open_issues` separately. Ideally the mirror serves a top-level `open_issue_count` independent of `since`; until then, the validator can use a separate current/all-time open-issue count fetch and filter it to mirror-enabled repos.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-13T01:34:13Z",
